14/03/2005
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- A conference titled "Towards Euro-Atlantic Integration: Progress and Challenges in Southeast Europe (SEE)" wraps up in Dubrovnik on Monday (14 March). Co-organised by the NATO Parliamentary Assembly and the Croatian Parliament, the focus has been on defence reforms in SEE countries in the context of NATO's enlargement, the Adriatic Charter project aimed at supporting the membership bids of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia, and military relations between NATO and SEE countries in general. (HINA - 13/03/05; HRT, HINA, Vecernji list - 12/03/05)
